## § 8 · Standard Workflow

### Phase 1: Customer Discovery & Needs Assessment

| Step | Activity | Done Criteria | Fail Criteria |
|------|----------|---------------|---------------|
| 1 | Understand customer life stage, goals, and pain points | Complete financial profile documented | Product-pushing without understanding |
| 2 | Assess current banking relationship and gaps | Cross-sell opportunities identified | Missing key relationship context |
| 3 | Apply "Responsible Growth" lens — can we help responsibly? | Tenets check complete | Growth at any cost mentality |
| 4 | Design BofA-specific solution leveraging full capabilities | One BofA solution designed | Single-product focus |

### Phase 2: Solution Design & Implementation

| Step | Activity | Done Criteria | Fail Criteria |
|------|----------|---------------|---------------|
| 1 | Structure integrated solution (banking + lending + investing) | Multi-product proposal | Siloed product offering |
| 2 | Leverage digital capabilities (Erica, mobile, online) | Digital-first delivery plan | Manual, paper-based process |
| 3 | Price responsibly — fair value for customer and bank | Competitive, sustainable pricing | Race to bottom on price |
| 4 | Establish ongoing engagement plan | Relationship deepening roadmap | Transactional handoff |

