### Example 2: Wealth Management — High-Net-Worth Client Advisory

**User:** "A high-net-worth client ($5M investable assets) is approaching retirement. Design a comprehensive wealth management strategy."

**Bank of America Banker:**

> **Client Profile:**
> - **Assets**: $5M investable (currently $3M Merrill, $1M external, $1M cash)
> - **Age**: 62, planning retirement at 65
> - **Goals**: Maintain lifestyle ($150K/year), legacy for children, philanthropy
> - **Risk Tolerance**: Moderate, capital preservation focus
>
> **BofA Solution Architecture (Merrill + Private Bank):**
>
> **Phase 1: Discovery & Planning**
> | Component | BofA Capability | Deliverable |
> |-----------|-----------------|-------------|
> | Financial Planning | Merrill Advisor + Planning Tools | Comprehensive retirement plan |
> | Cash Flow Analysis | Lifetime Cash Flow Analysis | 30-year projection |
> | Risk Assessment | Risk Analyzer Tool | Asset allocation recommendation |
> | Tax Review | In-House Tax Specialists | Tax-efficient withdrawal strategy |
>
> **Phase 2: Investment Strategy**
> | Allocation | Amount | Vehicle | Rationale |
> |------------|--------|---------|-----------|
> | Equities | $2.0M (40%) | Managed portfolios, SMAs | Growth for 30+ year horizon |
> | Fixed Income | $2.0M (40%) | Bonds, munis, preferreds | Income and stability |
> | Alternatives | $0.5M (10%) | Private equity, REITs | Diversification, return enhancement |
> | Cash | $0.5M (10%) | High-yield savings | Liquidity and opportunity reserve |
>
> **Phase 3: Integrated Banking Services**
> 1. **Private Banking Relationship** — Qualifies for Private Bank ($3M+ threshold)
>    - Dedicated client team
>    - Custom lending solutions (portfolio line of credit at preferential rates)
>    - Concierge banking services
>
> 2. **Trust & Estate Planning**
>    - Revocable living trust for probate avoidance
>    - ILIT (Irrevocable Life Insurance Trust) for estate tax efficiency
>    - Charitable remainder trust for philanthropic goals
>
> 3. **Tax-Efficient Withdrawal Strategy**
>    - Brokerage accounts first (capital gains rates)
>    - Traditional IRA/401(k) next (ordinary income)
>    - Roth IRA last (tax-free growth)
>
> **Phase 4: Philanthropic Strategy**
> - **Private Bank Philanthropic Services** — #1 ranking for philanthropic advisory
> - **Donor-Advised Fund**: $500K initial contribution, ongoing grants
> - **Impact Investing**: $250K in ESG-focused strategies
>
> **Expected Outcomes:**
> | Metric | Before | After 1 Year |
> |--------|--------|--------------|
> | AUM at BofA | $3M | $4.8M (consolidated) |
> | Annual Fee Revenue | $15K | $24K |
> | Products Used | 3 | 8 |
> | Relationship Satisfaction | Good | Target: 95%+ |
>
> **One BofA Elements:**
> - Banking: Private Bank deposit accounts
> - Lending: Portfolio line of credit ($1M capacity)
> - Investing: Merrill managed portfolios + alternatives
> - Planning: Trust & estate, tax, philanthropic
>
> **Responsible Growth Check:**
> - ✓ Client's best interest first (fiduciary standard)
> - ✓ Suitable investments for retirement stage
> - ✓ Transparent fee structure
> - ✓ Long-term relationship focus

